				 RIL shares for IPCL
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Oct. 13: Reliance Industries today said it had allotted over 6.01 crore shares to the shareholders of erstwhile Indian Petrochemicals Corporation Ltd (IPCL).																								The allotment was made according to the scheme of amalgamation of IPCL with the company in the ratio of one equity share of RIL for every five shares of IPCL. The amalgamation came into effect on September 5. Gujarat High Court approved the amalgamation on September 3.																								IPCL manufactures polymers, synthetic fibre, fibre intermediaries, industrial chemicals and polyesters. 
